---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Cost of Living Comparison for Expats | Compare Cities Worldwide"
description: "Compare cost of living between 14 major tech cities worldwide. See rent, groceries, transport, and dining costs side-by-side for Berlin, Amsterdam, London, and more."
---

{# Structured Data #}
{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "Cost of Living Comparison for Expats",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}/tools/cost-of-living/",
  "description": "{{ description }}",
  "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" }
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the cheapest European city for tech workers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Krakow, Poland and Tallinn, Estonia are among the most affordable European tech cities. Monthly costs for a single person start around €1,200-1,400, compared to €2,500+ in cities like Amsterdam or London. Both cities have growing tech sectors with visa sponsorship opportunities." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does rent cost in Berlin vs London?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A one-bedroom apartment in Berlin city center averages around €1,100/month, while the same in London costs approximately £2,100/month. Berlin rent is roughly 48% cheaper than London, making it one of the most attractive major European tech hubs for affordability." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Should I consider cost of living when choosing a relocation destination?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Absolutely. A higher salary doesn't always mean more purchasing power. For example, Zurich offers the highest tech salaries in Europe, but its cost of living is also the highest. Compare net salary (after tax) with living costs to understand your true financial situation." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What costs should I budget for when relocating?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Key costs include: rent (usually 30-40% of income), groceries, transportation, utilities, internet, health insurance, and dining. Don't forget one-time relocation costs like deposit (often 2-3 months rent), furniture, and registration fees. Many employers cover initial relocation expenses." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are these cost of living figures accurate?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Our data represents average costs as of early 2026 and is sourced from aggregated living cost databases. Actual costs vary by neighborhood, lifestyle, and personal choices. Use these figures as a starting point for planning, and research specific neighborhoods in your target city." }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{% block head %}
<style>
  .cost-bar { transition: width 0.5s ease-out; }
  .diff-positive { color: #16a34a; }
  .diff-negative { color: #dc2626; }
  .dark .diff-positive { color: #4ade80; }
  .dark .diff-negative { color: #f87171; }
</style>
{% endblock %}

